[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:11.071 --> 01:12.675
[BANGING]

01:25.786 --> 01:27.265
And so, heh...
Heh.

01:27.421 --> 01:32.029
I chose jellyfish as my favorite...

01:34.227 --> 01:36.229
[BABY COOING]

01:44.037 --> 01:46.039
[CHICKENS CLUCKING]

03:00.213 --> 03:01.851
You all fed? Yeah?

03:02.015 --> 03:03.995
Yeah...

03:25.872 --> 03:27.874
[FOOTSTEPS]

03:40.554 --> 03:42.033
[DOOR CLOSES]

04:23.196 --> 04:24.937
[DOOR OPENS]

04:25.899 --> 04:29.779
MAN:
Marcy! Marcy May!

04:29.936 --> 04:31.813
Where are you going?

04:32.706 --> 04:34.276
[DOOR CLOSES]

04:44.584 --> 04:46.586
[PANTING]

05:11.478 --> 05:13.958
[FOOTSTEPS RUNNING]

05:38.672 --> 05:40.674
[DOOR BELL JINGLING]

05:53.220 --> 05:56.861
WATTS:
Marcy, what are you doing here?

05:57.023 --> 05:59.128
Worried about you.

06:00.861 --> 06:02.863
Well, I'm fine.

06:04.030 --> 06:08.206
Yeah? And Patrick is worried about you.

06:08.802 --> 06:10.509
I just wanted to come into town.

06:11.538 --> 06:13.916
Oh, I could have given you a ride.

06:14.307 --> 06:15.911
I wanted to walk.

06:16.076 --> 06:17.817
Through the woods?

06:21.414 --> 06:22.893
Can I get you something?

06:23.049 --> 06:25.256
No, thank you.

06:25.719 --> 06:27.323
Are you done?

06:27.687 --> 06:29.530
Yeah.
Uh...

06:29.689 --> 06:31.600
You're not gonna finish that?

06:32.325 --> 06:34.066
Okay, thanks.

06:42.769 --> 06:43.839
Mm.

06:57.717 --> 06:59.287
Ready to go?

06:59.586 --> 07:01.429
Not right now.

07:03.723 --> 07:05.100
No?

07:18.204 --> 07:21.083
Hey, don't do that. Come here.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.219
You're shaking.

07:26.379 --> 07:28.120
Calm down.

07:32.585 --> 07:35.088
All right. You take care of yourself.

07:51.638 --> 07:54.915
[LINE RINGING]

08:00.013 --> 08:01.651
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]:
Hello?

08:03.249 --> 08:05.820
He Ho <i>?</i>

08:08.655 --> 08:11.659
<i>Martha?
Yeah.</i>

08:11.825 --> 08:14.931
<i>Where are you? Where have you been?</i>

08:17.330 --> 08:22.643
Uh, I'm not sure. I'm upstate, I think.

08:22.802 --> 08:24.509
<i>You're in New York?</i>

08:24.671 --> 08:26.810
Yeah, I think.

08:26.973 --> 08:29.112
<i>When did you get back?</i>

08:29.275 --> 08:31.516
<i>How long have you been here?</i>

08:32.712 --> 08:34.316
Martha?

08:34.847 --> 08:36.691
<i>Martha, what's wrong?</i>

08:36.850 --> 08:39.159
I don't know. Um...

08:39.352 --> 08:42.128
I should go back.

08:42.288 --> 08:44.290
<i>Go back where?</i>

08:45.291 --> 08:48.898
<i>Martha, what happened? Are you okay?</i>

08:49.062 --> 08:52.407
Um, I have to go. Um...

08:52.632 --> 08:54.373
I can't stay gone, so...

08:54.534 --> 08:56.070
<i>No, no, no, don't go.</i>

08:56.236 --> 08:58.409
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

09:00.507 --> 09:02.009
<i>Martha.</i>

09:02.375 --> 09:03.718
I'm sorry for calling.

09:03.877 --> 09:06.153
<i>Please don't hang up.
Don't hang up the phone.</i>

09:06.312 --> 09:08.986
<i>Find out where you are
and! will come get you.</i>

09:11.584 --> 09:14.224
Martha?
I can't wait that long.

09:14.387 --> 09:17.493
<i>What do you mean? Tell me where you are
and I will come right now.</i>

09:17.657 --> 09:20.069
No, it's okay, you don't have to.

09:20.226 --> 09:23.230
<i>Martha, I wanna see you. Please.</i>

09:23.897 --> 09:25.535
Martha?

09:26.332 --> 09:28.005
<i>Martha.</i>

09:42.348 --> 09:43.884
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

09:58.765 --> 10:01.371
I made you some tea.
Thanks.

10:06.773 --> 10:09.879
You're dripping everywhere.

10:15.615 --> 10:18.960
Ted should be up from the city soon,
make us some dinner.

10:19.119 --> 10:20.462
I'm pretty tired.

10:20.620 --> 10:23.157
Is it okay if I just go to bed?

10:25.658 --> 10:27.137
Sure.

10:28.294 --> 10:31.832
Get a good night's sleep tonight
and you'll be as good as new tomorrow.

10:44.978 --> 10:46.252
[DOOR CLOSES]

10:49.616 --> 10:51.186
[SIGHS]

10:58.825 --> 11:00.327
[DOOR OPENS]

11:03.163 --> 11:04.437
[DOOR CLOSES]

11:04.597 --> 11:07.009
Hi.
TED: Hey.

11:10.303 --> 11:11.509
<i>Hey.)'...</i>

11:16.342 --> 11:19.812
Well?
She seems okay.

11:21.447 --> 11:23.723
What did she say?
Not much.

11:23.883 --> 11:25.487
She's really tired.

11:25.652 --> 11:26.824
Yeah?
Yeah.

11:26.986 --> 11:28.727
Where's she been?

11:29.189 --> 11:32.329
She had some boyfriend.
They were living in the Catskills.

11:32.492 --> 11:34.870
What?
It's okay.

11:35.028 --> 11:37.201
Heh, it's not really, Lucy.
It's fine.

11:37.363 --> 11:39.866
She's here now.

11:40.033 --> 11:41.671
Hmm.

11:43.069 --> 11:45.549
How long is she gonna be staying again?
Ha-ha-ha!

11:52.045 --> 11:53.888
TED:
Oh, Martha.

11:55.748 --> 11:58.092
Welcome.
Hi.

12:00.220 --> 12:03.099
Great to finally meet you.
Yeah.

12:04.023 --> 12:05.900
Did you sleep all right?
Mm-hm.

12:06.059 --> 12:07.402
Good.

12:08.061 --> 12:10.268
So how do you like our house?

12:10.430 --> 12:12.341
It's nice.

12:13.833 --> 12:16.837
It's just a rental.
Yeah, well, I love it.

12:17.003 --> 12:18.676
Mm.

12:19.505 --> 12:23.351
I didn't know there was <i>a</i> lake.
Mm. Yeah.

12:23.943 --> 12:25.513
Do you still like to swim?

12:25.678 --> 12:27.954
You don't still live in the city?
TED & LUCY: Heh, heh.

12:28.114 --> 12:32.062
We do. We just like to come up here
on weekends and holidays.

12:36.756 --> 12:39.532
You know. Ted is working
on this new building downtown...

12:39.692 --> 12:41.262
and as soon as it's finished...

12:41.427 --> 12:44.567
we're taking one of the apartments.
Do you wanna see pictures?

12:47.100 --> 12:49.740
Do you think she's excited
to have you back?

12:52.071 --> 12:55.450
This is just the view, and obviously
the interiors aren't finished...

12:55.608 --> 12:58.555
but it's nice, right?
MARTHA: Mm-hm.

12:59.145 --> 13:01.284
We were supposed to move in
in the spring...

13:01.447 --> 13:04.985
but, uh, construction was halted, so
it's gonna be just a little while longer.

13:05.151 --> 13:10.100
Yes, just a little while longer.
Okay, sorry, no more work talk.

13:12.892 --> 13:14.769
Aren't you hungry?

13:15.395 --> 13:17.932
Not really, sorry.
Well, you have to eat something.

13:18.097 --> 13:21.408
It's okay,
I can make you something later.

13:28.341 --> 13:30.150
Where are we?

13:30.476 --> 13:32.149
Connecticut.

13:35.315 --> 13:37.295
Well, how far are we?

13:38.318 --> 13:40.696
From what?
Yesterday.

13:43.756 --> 13:46.259
You mean from where I picked you up?

13:47.660 --> 13:50.197
About three hours. Why?

13:50.930 --> 13:52.671
I was just wondering.

13:57.003 --> 13:59.005
[HAMMER BANGING]

14:04.177 --> 14:06.179
[HAMMER BANGING]

14:11.484 --> 14:13.157
Put out your cigarette.
Why?

14:13.319 --> 14:14.957
Just do it.

14:16.856 --> 14:18.233
Is that him?
Yeah.

14:18.391 --> 14:19.699
<i>Hey.)'...</i>

14:19.859 --> 14:21.133
PATRICK:
Is this Martha?

14:21.294 --> 14:22.637
Hi.

14:23.129 --> 14:25.803
How you doing?
Great.

14:25.965 --> 14:28.809
Oh, you've got a really nice place here.

14:28.968 --> 14:31.710
It's as much yours as it is mine.

14:32.038 --> 14:34.917
I thought you quit.
I did.

14:35.074 --> 14:36.747
I worry for you.

14:36.909 --> 14:38.479
I know.

14:40.880 --> 14:42.723
I'm sorry.

14:43.349 --> 14:46.228
Don't apologize to me. It's your body.

14:50.690 --> 14:54.729
Zoe, look after this girl.

14:54.994 --> 14:58.066
For once in her life,
she deserves some real care.

14:58.264 --> 14:59.402
I will.

14:59.565 --> 15:01.511
She's been great.

15:01.667 --> 15:05.080
Everyone's been really great.
Good.

15:06.439 --> 15:08.248
Martha.

15:10.543 --> 15:12.921
You look like a Marcy May.

15:13.246 --> 15:14.748
Marcy was my grandmother's name.

15:14.914 --> 15:17.588
Wow, there you go.
Heh.

15:24.891 --> 15:26.928
TED:
I'm going in. Do you wanna join'?

15:27.093 --> 15:28.595
Sure.

15:31.697 --> 15:35.042
You coming?
In a minute.

16:22.915 --> 16:24.861
Martha!

16:35.795 --> 16:38.036
That is an interesting choice
of swim wear.

16:38.197 --> 16:40.177
Martha, get out of the water.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.843
What?
LUCY: Get out of the water.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.778
Why aren't you wearing any clothes?
What is wrong with you?

16:45.938 --> 16:48.145
You can't do that around here, you know.
MARTHA: Why?

16:48.307 --> 16:50.378
Because there are kids around.
People come by.

16:50.543 --> 16:52.853
MARTHA: So?
You just can't, okay? Get out of the water.

16:53.012 --> 16:55.356
We don't do that kind of thing. Get out.

16:58.684 --> 17:01.688
You could have asked me.
I have a bathing suit you could borrow.

17:01.854 --> 17:04.198
What's wrong with you? Jesus.

18:23.703 --> 18:24.807
MAX:
Hey, hey, Marcy.

18:24.971 --> 18:26.279
Max.
MAX: Hey.

18:26.439 --> 18:28.316
Where do they go at night?
Uh...

18:28.474 --> 18:31.944
Pfft! I don't know. Heh.
I never get invited.

18:37.483 --> 18:39.759
You wanna have a drink with me?

18:40.620 --> 18:42.258
They won't be back for a few hours.

18:42.421 --> 18:46.961
I shouldn't. I'm not gonna drink for a while, actually.
I think it's a good idea for me.

18:47.126 --> 18:48.628
All right.

18:50.796 --> 18:52.571
[GRUNTS]

18:55.401 --> 18:58.245
[CLANGING]

18:58.738 --> 19:00.911
Wake up, everybody.

19:04.276 --> 19:05.949
Good morning.

19:37.977 --> 19:43.017
We switch out jobs each day
so we all know how to do different things.

19:43.182 --> 19:45.184
Do you knit?
No.

19:45.351 --> 19:47.524
I can learn, though.
Oh, no, that's okay.

19:47.687 --> 19:49.564
You'll find your role.

19:49.722 --> 19:53.864
It takes time for people
to find their role in a new family.

19:55.461 --> 19:59.238
Mostly, we sell blankets in town
because we still need some money.

19:59.398 --> 20:03.175
But once the farm is up and running,
we'll be self-sufficient...

20:03.335 --> 20:06.373
and we'll never have
to worry about it again.

20:07.640 --> 20:10.883
[HUMMING]

20:25.024 --> 20:26.560
Hey. I'm sorry, Patrick. Hey.

20:26.726 --> 20:29.036
PATRICK: What are you sorry for'?
Ahem.

20:29.195 --> 20:31.072
Um, here.

20:31.430 --> 20:32.932
How are you, man?

20:33.099 --> 20:34.510
Good, you?

20:34.667 --> 20:36.271
Feels like...

20:37.103 --> 20:40.277
It's a really great consistency.
ZOE: Yeah, and it's sticky.

20:40.439 --> 20:43.352
And it holds together like glue.

20:43.509 --> 20:46.456
And it can flow around. Like...
WATTS: You should talk to her.

20:46.612 --> 20:48.717
That's why I need to
figure out how to do it.

20:48.881 --> 20:50.053
Yeah.

20:50.516 --> 20:53.463
Yeah, you'll figure it out. Don't look...

20:53.619 --> 20:56.566
PATRICK: How's everything going so far,
Marcy May?

20:56.889 --> 20:59.426
Good.
PATRICK: Do you like it here?

20:59.592 --> 21:01.902
Yeah, it's... It's great.

21:02.061 --> 21:03.563
PATRICK:
I want you to feel at home.

21:03.729 --> 21:06.972
I do, thank you.
PATRICK: Mm-hm.

21:07.433 --> 21:09.777
I know people have abandoned you
your whole life.

21:09.935 --> 21:12.438
Your father.
What?

21:12.772 --> 21:15.446
I don't blame you
for not trusting people.

21:17.576 --> 21:20.785
But if you're ever going to have
a meaningful relationship...

21:21.614 --> 21:23.821
you need to let your guard down.

21:24.650 --> 21:27.096
It's not your fault, but it's there.

21:28.387 --> 21:32.062
And if you feel safe here,
and I hope you do, let us in.

21:33.292 --> 21:35.135
We wanna help you.

21:35.461 --> 21:38.999
Yeah. We think you're fucking awesome.

21:39.732 --> 21:41.939
PATRICK:
But if you're gonna live here...

21:43.803 --> 21:46.079
you need to be a part of things.

21:58.484 --> 21:59.656
Play another song.

21:59.819 --> 22:01.765
[ALL CHUCKLE]

22:02.421 --> 22:05.834
MAN: Do "A Patch of Land."
It's not a song.

22:05.991 --> 22:08.130
[ALL LAUGH]

22:08.294 --> 22:10.205
[GUITARS PLAYING]

22:12.665 --> 22:14.372
Good morning.
Good morning.

22:14.533 --> 22:16.672
How are you feeling today?
Good.

22:16.836 --> 22:19.316
Yeah? Good.

22:19.471 --> 22:24.216
So, uh, I stopped by the juice place
and I got you a kale with ginseng.

22:24.376 --> 22:27.550
Do you mind just putting your feet
off the counter?

22:28.013 --> 22:30.687
I got you a kale and ginseng
because it's just...

22:30.850 --> 22:33.330
I don't know,
I thought it might make you feel better.

22:34.019 --> 22:36.829
If that doesn't appeal to you,
I also got a pineapple orange.

22:36.989 --> 22:39.902
Yeah, that might be better. Thank you.
Okay.

22:40.059 --> 22:44.530
Oh, and I also got you protein bars,
just in case you want a snack.

22:48.968 --> 22:51.244
Why is the house so big?

22:51.871 --> 22:53.578
The house isn't so big.

22:53.739 --> 22:55.912
It's big for two people.

22:56.075 --> 22:58.749
Well, yeah, but we like to entertain.

22:58.911 --> 23:01.221
And sometimes friends come up
for the weekend...

23:01.380 --> 23:04.156
sometimes we have parties.
It's just nice to have space.

23:04.316 --> 23:06.523
So no one else lives here?

23:06.685 --> 23:09.188
Of course no one else lives here.

23:27.506 --> 23:30.214
You're married?
Yeah.

23:30.376 --> 23:33.380
When?
April.

23:34.947 --> 23:38.121
I tried calling you, but, uh, apparently
you got rid of your cell phone.

23:38.284 --> 23:39.854
I lost it.

23:40.019 --> 23:43.262
You didn't think to get a new one?
I got used to not having one.

23:43.422 --> 23:45.561
TED: Cocktails, anyone?
No, thank you.

23:45.724 --> 23:48.204
Martha?
Mm-mm.

23:52.965 --> 23:56.071
Was it a big wedding?
About 40 people.

23:56.235 --> 23:57.771
Mostly Ted's family.

23:57.937 --> 24:00.281
Did Aunt Dora come?
Ha, yes.

24:00.439 --> 24:03.113
Did she smoke like a chimney
and complain about everything?

24:03.275 --> 24:05.812
She's not that bad.
You didn't have to live with her.

24:05.978 --> 24:07.116
TED:
You lived with Dora?

24:07.279 --> 24:09.452
She lived with me after Mom died.

24:10.049 --> 24:12.427
And where were you?
LUCY: College.

24:12.584 --> 24:13.927
Huh.

24:14.787 --> 24:17.131
LUCY: She'd love to know you're okay.
MARTHA: She hates me.

24:17.289 --> 24:18.791
LUCY:
She does not hate you.

24:18.958 --> 24:20.631
Look at me. Come on.
MARTHA: Mm-mm.

24:20.793 --> 24:23.569
No.
LUCY: I don't have any pictures of you.

24:25.264 --> 24:27.073
God, you're gorgeous.

24:27.232 --> 24:29.769
It's really rather irritating.

24:29.935 --> 24:31.141
There you go.

24:31.303 --> 24:33.340
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

24:36.675 --> 24:39.519
You don't need to shake it.
That's a myth.

24:42.281 --> 24:44.989
Is it true married people don't fuck?
LUCY: What?

24:47.252 --> 24:48.754
No, heh.

24:51.790 --> 24:53.360
Excuse me.

25:05.004 --> 25:06.347
Put this on.
You're kidding.

25:06.505 --> 25:09.179
Your clothes are disgusting. Try it.
Why does it matter?

25:09.341 --> 25:12.652
Because it feels good to put on
something nice and comfortable.

25:31.797 --> 25:33.970
It looks really good on you,
you little shit.

25:34.133 --> 25:37.205
Whatever makes you happy, mama bear.

25:41.573 --> 25:44.918
You're making fun of me,
and I think it looks really good on you.

25:47.713 --> 25:49.715
[CHUCKLES]

25:54.753 --> 25:58.724
What, ifs not good?
No, no, it's fine.

25:59.091 --> 26:01.230
[CHUCKLES]

26:01.760 --> 26:05.902
Uh, it's a bit dry.
It's not dry.

26:06.065 --> 26:09.205
It just needs a little bit more salt,
that's all.

26:09.368 --> 26:12.542
[ALL CHUCKLING]

26:16.442 --> 26:19.912
She seems better today.
Yeah.

26:20.279 --> 26:22.418
I wish I didn't have to go tomorrow.

26:22.581 --> 26:25.460
Well, let me take you.
No.

26:26.085 --> 26:28.588
I don't want her to be alone.

26:30.255 --> 26:32.701
You'll be nice to her, right?

26:33.425 --> 26:36.031
I'm always nice.
Oh.

26:36.195 --> 26:38.141
[CHUCKLING]

26:55.114 --> 26:57.116
[PATRICK GRUNTING]

27:06.391 --> 27:07.961
[GRUNTING]

27:46.665 --> 27:50.340
I know you feel like something bad
just happened, Marcy May.

27:51.603 --> 27:54.607
But you have to trust me,
that wasn't bad.

27:55.474 --> 27:57.681
That was truly good.

27:59.511 --> 28:02.014
We've all been in this situation.

28:04.516 --> 28:08.020
We wouldn't all still be here
if what happened in that room was bad.

28:09.521 --> 28:12.365
We all love each other very much.

28:12.858 --> 28:15.304
We're all together on this.

28:16.495 --> 28:18.702
You have to trust us.

28:20.199 --> 28:21.974
Do you believe me?

28:25.804 --> 28:27.181
Yeah.

28:48.093 --> 28:50.164
You're so lucky.

28:52.831 --> 28:55.334
I'd give anything
to have my first time again.

28:55.500 --> 28:58.242
Really?
Yeah.

28:58.770 --> 29:00.681
It's so special.

29:01.907 --> 29:04.615
I can't remember anything.

29:05.711 --> 29:10.922
I just woke up and felt this pain.

29:11.083 --> 29:13.063
That's the cleansing.

29:13.752 --> 29:17.427
It's good. It means it's working
if you can't remember things.

29:18.257 --> 29:22.034
You're cleansing yourself of the past
and the toxins.

29:24.296 --> 29:26.242
You need to share yourself.

29:26.398 --> 29:27.934
Don't be selfish.

29:28.100 --> 29:29.773
I'm not.

29:30.035 --> 29:32.208
So smile, then.

29:32.604 --> 29:34.948
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

29:35.240 --> 29:38.744
Enjoy this amazing night.
It only happens once.

29:51.623 --> 29:53.796
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

29:54.092 --> 29:57.266
[HUMMING]

30:09.341 --> 30:10.911
Thanks.

30:12.311 --> 30:15.019
Is that a new one, Max?
There's one right there.

30:15.180 --> 30:17.490
Yeah. Is that <i>a</i> new song?

30:17.649 --> 30:19.185
Yeah, I wrote it yesterday.

30:19.351 --> 30:20.921
That was the first half.
Great.

30:21.086 --> 30:22.997
That was nice.
Thanks, man.

30:23.155 --> 30:24.634
Yeah.

30:34.199 --> 30:36.839
All right. This is called "Marcy's Song."

30:38.103 --> 30:41.607
[GUITAR PLAYING]

30:51.049 --> 30:53.325
[SINGING] Well, she's

30:53.485 --> 30:56.295
<i>She's just a picture</i>

